          <div id="Circulation">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">The General Overall News</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">In other news, Sunday Mirror reporter, Emma McMenamy has been shortlisted for the Irish Justice Media Awards. Her outstanding work includes an exclusive interview with Sinead Connolly, a brave victim of a gun attack. Emma spoke to the mum of one Sinead about facing her attackers in court and how she won't let them win, despite being left paralysed after a bullet hit her spine. Emma's nomination is for the Irish Sunday Mirror and the Irish Mirror online. We're also thrilled for Ciaran Bradley and Mostafa Darwish, who has been nominated in the broadcast category for their outstanding work on the Homeless Ireland series. Their reporting sheds light on the issue of homelessness, bringing attention to those in need. 

<br><br>From a circulation standpoint, May has been a good month despite some challenges. Reach titles in NI increased cover price at the start of the month, along with two Bank Holiday issues to contend with due to King Charles's Coronation. Coverage of the Local Council elections delivered a sales uplift of 7% wow, whilst the free Paddy Power golf bets on the US PGA increased sales by 2.5%-3%. Hopefully, the end of the Premier League season should give a strong finish to the month.

<br><br>Finally, after an incredible 28 years, we bid farewell to Kevan 'Furby' Furbank, who leaves Reach. Kevan was integral to building the Irish Editorial production right from the very start. He was also a dab hand as our resident 'geetar' man and entertainer at all our think tanks over the years and almost got us to the no 1 slot with 'we wish you a Mirror Christmas'! He leaves with our best wishes to both him and Lizzie and will have the time now to do much more travelling, drinking a fine red, cooking, writing, reading, and of course spending time with his beloved girls.. Good luck, Furby! You will be greatly missed by all of us at Reach. </p>             
